# Shoppershala Project Rules

## Before You Code
1. Read `CLAUDE.md` for full project context
2. Read this file for behavioral rules
3. Check existing files before creating new ones
4. Run `pnpm lint` and `pnpm test` before/after changes

## Backend Rules
- Use `#utils/`, `#models/`, `#services/`, `#controllers/`, `#routes/`, `#middlewares/`, `#config/` subpath imports (NEVER relative paths)
- Keep layered architecture: routes → controllers → services → models
- Add Zod validation schemas for all new POST/PATCH endpoints
- Use Winston logger (`#utils/logger.js`), never console.log
- All new endpoints go under `/api/v1/`

## Frontend Rules
- Use the `api.js` utility for all API calls (wraps axios with JWT interceptor)
- Use Zustand for client-side state, TanStack Query for server state
- Tailwind v4 for styling (utility classes + CSS, no separate CSS files for components)
- Never import React unnecessarily (React 19 auto-jsx)

## Git Rules
- Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`, `docs:`, `test:`
- Run `pnpm format` before committing to fix formatting
- Commit messages must pass commitlint conventional config

## Testing Rules
- Write tests for new backend services/models
- Tests use Vitest, co-located with source files
- Ensure MongoDB is running (`docker compose up -d`) before integration tests
